processStep.description: -3348174 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN-

instructions.line: 3348174 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-581 TO LIFT ENGINE.

processStep.description: -3348175 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN-

instructions.line: 3348175 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-581 TO LIFT ENGINE.

processStep.description: -3331168 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN-

instructions.line: 3331168 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-581 TO LIFT ENGINE.

processStep.description: -3357367 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN-

instructions.line: 3357367 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-581 TO LIFT ENGINE.

processStep.description: -3357368 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN-

instructions.line: 3357367 ENGINE AR-STANDARD TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-581 TO LIFT ENGINE.

processStep.description: FUEL LINE CONNECTIONS TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: FUEL LINE CONNECTIONS TO ENGINE TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW TO FUEL PUMP LOCATED ON TOP RH REAR OF ENGINE
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO ELBOW.
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW TO FUEL RETURN LOCATED TO THE LEFT OF THE
FUEL PUMP. ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THIS ELBOW.

processStep.description: SECURE ENGINE FUEL LINES TITAN

instructions.line: SECURE ENGINE FUEL LINES TITAN
SECURE THE 2 FUEL LINES ASSEMBLED TO THE TOP RH SIDE OF THE
ENGINE TO THE PLATE LOCATED ON THE BACK RH CORNER WITH 2 CLIPS,
1 BOLT, 1 WASHER AND 1 SPACER.
ASSEMBLE 1 UNION IN EACH LINE.

processStep.description: -ETHER AID BRKT & HOSES TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: -ETHER AID BRACKET AND HOSES TO ENGINE
ASSEMBLE 1 BRACKET ASSEMBLY TO THE TOP FRONT CENTER OF THE
ENGINE USING 1 EXISTING BOLT ORIENT BRACKET SLIGHTLY TO THE LEFT
OF THE ENGINE.
ASSEMBLE 3 HOSSES TO TEE ASSEMBLEY AND CLIP TO THE FRONT OF THE
PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED BRACKET WITH 2 CLIPS, 2 BOLTS AND 2
WASHERS. THE REMAINDER OF THE FRONT HOSE WILL BE CLIPPED TO THE
THE TRUCK. THE 2 HOSES ON THE SIDES WILL BE CLIPPED IN LATER
OPERATIONS.
NOTE: TORQUE TO 1E0279A, B & P

processStep.description: -ETHER AID BRKT & HOSES TO ENGINE-LRC T

instructions.line: -ETHER AID BRKT & HOSES TO ENGINE-LRC T
ASSEMBLE 1 BRACKET ASSEMBLY TO THE TOP FRONT CENTER OF THE
ENGINE USING 1 EXISTING BOLT ORIENT BRACKET SLIGHTLY TO THE LEFT
OF THE ENGINE.
ASSEMBLE 3 HOSSES TO TEE ASSEMBLEY AND CLIP TO THE FRONT OF THE
PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED BRACKET WITH 2 CLIPS, 2 BOLTS AND 2
WASHERS. THE REMAINDER OF THE FRONT HOSE WILL BE CLIPPED TO THE
THE TRUCK. THE 2 HOSES ON THE SIDES WILL BE CLIPPED IN LATER
OPERATIONS.

processStep.description: ATTACH ETHER AID HOSES TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: ATTACH ETHER AID HOSES TO ENGINE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW & 1 NOZZLE TO 1 CONNECTOR AND ATTACH TO LH TUBE
ON ENGINE. CONNECT PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED HOSE TO ELBOW.
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW & 1 NOZZLE TO 1 CONNECTOR AND ATTACH TO RH TUBE
ON ENGINE. CONNECT PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED HOSE TO ELBOW.

component.note: POSITION THE FINAL INSTALLATION SUCH THAT THE ORIFICE SPRAY
INDICATION MARK IS DIRECTED AGAINST THE THE INCOMING AIR STREAM.

processStep.description: ATTACH ETHER AID HOSES TO ENGINE-LRC TTN

instructions.line: ATTACH ETHER AID HOSES TO ENGINE-LRC TTN
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW & 1 NOZZLE TO 1 CONNECTOR AND ATTACH TO LH TUBE
ON ENGINE. CONNECT PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED HOSE TO ELBOW.
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW & 1 NOZZLE TO 1 CONNECTOR AND ATTACH TO RH TUBE
ON ENGINE. CONNECT PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED HOSE TO ELBOW.
SECURE TO ENGINE WITH 2 CLIP, 2 SPACER, 2 BOLT & 2 WASHER.

component.note: POSITION THE FINAL INSTALLATION SUCH THAT THE ORIFICE SPRAY
INDICATION MARK IS DIRECTED AGAINST THE THE INCOMING AIR STREAM.

processStep.description: ASSEMBLE HARNESS AND PLATE TO ENGINE-TTN

instructions.line: ASSEMBLE HARNESS AND PLATE TO ENGINE-TTN
ASSEMBLE 1 PLATE TO FRONT OF ENGINE WITH 2 CLIP, 2 CLIP, 2
STRAP, 2 WASHER (NO BOLTS CALLED OUT ON PRINT)
ASSEMBLE THE SQUARE BREAKOUT FROM THE HARNESS AND CONNECT TO THE
ECM ON THE LH SIDE OF ENGINE AND TWO OTHER BREAKOUTS TO HARNESS
DIRECTLY ABOVE ECM.
SECURE HARNESS TO ENGINE WITH 1 CLIP, 2 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 1 CLIP & 2
STRAP.
USE EXISTING ENGINE HARDWARE.

processStep.description: -WIRING HARNESS TO FRONT LH ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: -WIRING HARNESS TO FRONT LH ENGINE-TITAN
SECURE HARNESS TO LH SIDE OF ENGINE WITH 3 CLIP, 2 CLIP, 1 BOLT,
2 WASHER, 2 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 1 WASHER, 1 BOLT, 1 WASHER & 7 STRAP.
ASSEMBLE THE RESPECTIVE LEADS TO THE ALTERNATOR AND A/C
COMPRESSOR. SECURE THE BOOT ON THE ALTERNATOR LEAD TO THE
HARNESS WITH 1 STRAP.
REFERENCE VIS AID FOR EXACT LOCATIONS.

processStep.description: WIRING HARNESS TO REAR OF ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: WIRING HARNESS TO REAR OF ENGINE-TITAN
SECURE PREVIOUSLY INSTALLED HARNESS TO REAR OF ENGINE WITH 3
CLIP, 3 CLIP, 4 CLIP, 7 STRAP, 1 BOLT & 1 WASHER.
ASSEMBLE 1 SPEED SENSOR TO TORQUE CONVERTER.
LEAD ON THE RH SIDE WILL BRANCH OFF. CONNECT 1 LEAD TO THE
SPEED SENSOR AND THE OTHER END TO THE STARTER.
REFERNCE VIS AID FOR ORIENTATION AND LOCATION OF THE HARNESS.

processStep.description: -TORQUE CONVERTER TO ENGINE TITAN-

instructions.line: -TORQUE CONVERTER TO ENGINE TITAN-
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-7567 TO LIFT TQ CONVERTER
INSTALL 2 GUIDE PINS. AFTER GEAR LINES UP, REMOVE GUIDE PINS
BEFORE DRAWING IN.
ASSEM 1 SEAL, 1 SEAL & 1 RING TO TORQUE CONVERTER SUB &
CONVERTER SUB & 1 STRAP TO BOTTOM OF CONVERTER, WITH 16 BOLT &
16 WASHER.
PLEASE NOTE: POSITION TEE ON TORQUE CONVERTER ACROSS LIFTING
EYE HOLE AFTER TORQUE CONVERTER IS INSTALLED. TEE SHOULD BE
PARALLEL TO BACK OF TORQUE CONVERTER.
INSTALL 1 PLUG AND 1 SEAL UNTILL PORT IS NEEDED.
RECORD SERIAL NUMBER ON TORQUE CONVERTER INTO MES TRACEABILITY.
TORQUE 1E279A

component.note: NOTE A: LUBRICATE BORE LIGHTLY WITH LUBRICANT BEING SEALED.

processStep.description: WIRING HARNESS TO TORQUE CONVERTER-TITAN

instructions.line: WIRING HARNESS TO TORQUE CONVERTER-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 PLATE WITH 1 BOLT & 1 WASHER TO LH SIDE OF TC.
SECURE PREVIOUSLY ROUTED HARNESS TO PLATE AND TORQUE CONVERTER
WITH 3 CLIP, 3 CLIP, 1 CLIP & 7 STRAP. USE EXISTING HARDWARE.
ASSEMBLE 3 SENSOR GP TO LH SIDE OF TORQUE CONVERTER.

processStep.description: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [120 VOLT]-

instructions.line: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [120 VOLT]
BOLTS.ASSEMBLE 1 CAP TO 1 ELEMENT AND ASSEMBLE IT TO ADAPTER -
JACKET. ASSEMBLE SECOND SET OF ELEMENT AND CAP ON RIGHT SIDE
AFTER REMOVING PLUG.
TORQUE TO 1E279A&B
CORD TO BE SHIP WITH FIELD ASSEMBLY PARTS.

component.note: NOTE: CAP AS TO BE USED TO PROTECT TERMINALS WHEN CORD AS IS
NOTE: FOR USE WITH 120 VOLT GROUNDED POWER SOURCE

processStep.description: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [240 VOLT]-

instructions.line: HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [240 VOLT]
BOLTS.ASSEMBLE 1 CAP TO 1 ELEMENT AND ASSEMBLE IT TO ADAPTER -
JACKET. ASSEMBLE SECOND SET OF ELEMENT AND CAP ON RIGHT SIDE
AFTER REMOVING PLUG.
TORQUE TO 1E279A&B
CORD TO BE SHIP WITH FIELD ASSEMBLY PARTS.

component.note: NOTE: CAP AS TO BE USED TO PROTECT TERMINALS WHEN CORD AS IS
NOTE: FOR USE WITH 120 VOLT GROUNDED POWER SOURCE

processStep.description: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [120 VOLT]-

instructions.line: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [120 VOLT]
REMOVE PLATE ON LEFT SIDE OF ENGINE. GATHER 1ADAPTER-JACKET AND
1 GASKET AND ASSEMBLE TO OPENING WITH 1 BOLT AND 5
BOLTS.ASSEMBLE 1 CAP TO 1 ELEMENT AND ASSEMBLE IT TO ADAPTER -
JACKET. ASSEMBLE SECOND SET OF ELEMENT AND CAP ON RIGHT SIDE
AFTER REMOVING PLUG.
TORQUE TO 1E279A&B
CORD TO BE SHIP WITH FIELD ASSEMBLY PARTS.

component.note: NOTE: CAP AS TO BE USED TO PROTECT TERMINALS WHEN CORD AS IS
NOTE: FOR USE WITH 120 VOLT GROUNDED POWER SOURCE

processStep.description: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [240 VOLT].

instructions.line: -HEATER GP-JACKET WATER [240 VOLT].
REMOVE PLATE ON LEFT SIDE OF ENGINE. GATHER 1 ADAPTER-JACKET AND
1 GASKET AND ASSEMBLE TO OPENINGWITH 1 BOLT AND 5 BOLTS.ASSEMBLE
1 CAP TO 1 ELEMENT AND ASSEMBLE IT INTO ADAPTER-JACKET. ASSEMBLE
SECOND ELEMENT AND CAP INTO RIGHT SIDE AFTER PLUG IS REMOVED.
TORQUE TO 1E279A&B
cORD TO BE SHIPPED WITH FIELD ASSEMBLY PARTS.

component.note: NOTE: CAP AS TO BE USED TO PROTECT TERMINALS WHEN CORD AS IS
NOTE: FOR USE WITH 120 VOLT GROUNDED POWER SOURCE

processStep.description: LH STARTER TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: LH STARTER TO ENGINE-TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE PED 83-7669 TO LIFT STARTER INTO PLACE
ASSEMBLE 1 STARTER TO LH REAR ENGINE JUST IN FRONT OF THE TORQUE
CONVERTER WITH 1 GASKET AND 3 BOLTS.
NOTE: TORQUE TO 1E0279A

processStep.description: RH STARTER TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: RH STARTER TO ENGINE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 STARTER MOTOR TO THE RH SIDE OF THE ENGINE JUST IN
FRONT OF THE TORQUE CONVERTER WITH 1 GASKET AND 3 BOLTS.
NOTE: TORQUE TO 1E0279A

processStep.description: TRANS OIL COOLER ELBOW TO FRONT COOLER

instructions.line: TRANS OIL COOLER ELBOW TO FRONT COOLER
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW SUB TO FRONT OF OIL COOLER AT BOTTOM
RH SIDE OF ENGINE WITH 1 GASKET, 3 BOLTS, 1 BOLT & 4 WASHER.

processStep.description: -TRANS OIL COOLER ELBOW TO BACK COOLER

instructions.line: TRANS OIL COOLER ELBOW TO BACK COOLER
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW SUB TO BACK SIDE OF OIL COOLER AT BOTTOM
RH SIDE OF ENGINE WITH 1 GASKET, 3 BOLT, 1 BOLT & 4 WASHER.

processStep.description: -OIL PAN GAGE-TITAN-

instructions.line: -OIL PAN GAGE-TITAN-
ASSEMBLE 1 GAGE AS TO ENGINE AND SECURE WITH 1 BRACKET, 1 CLIP,
1 BOLT, 2 WASHER & 1 NUT.

processStep.description: -OIL FILL TUBE TO ENGINE RM695-TITAN

instructions.line: -OIL FILL TUBE TO ENGINE RM695-
REMOVE COVER ON RIGHT FRONT OF ENGINE & ASSEMBLE OIL FILL TUBE
SUB WITH 1 SEAL, 2 BOLTS, & 2 WASHERS.

processStep.description: ROCKFORD FAN DRIVE GP TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: ROCKFORD FAN DRIVE GP TO ENGINE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 DRIVE FAN SUB TO ENGINE WITH 3 BOLT, 1 BOLT & 4
WASHER.
ASSEMBLE 1 PULLY TO ENGINE WITH 4 BOLT & 4 WASHER.

processStep.description: ROCKFORD FAN DRIVE GP TO ENGINE-TITAN

instructions.line: ROCKFORD FAN DRIVE GP TO ENGINE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 DRIVE FAN SUB TO ENGINE WITH 3 BOLT, 1 BOLT & 4
WASHER.
ASSEMBLE 1 PULLY TO ENGINE WITH 4 BOLT & 4 WASHER.

processStep.description: HARNESS TO DRIVE FAN-TITAN

instructions.line: HARNESS TO DRIVE FAN-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 HARNESS TO DRIVE FAN AND ENGINE. SECURE TO
PREVIOUSLY ASSEMBLED CLIP ON DRIVE FAN AND TO ENGNE WITH 2
STRAP.

processStep.description: -AIR COMPRESSOR TO ENGINE-TITAN-

instructions.line: -AIR COMPRESSOR TO ENGINE-TITAN-
ASSEMBLE 1 COMPRESSOR GP TO ENGINE WITH 1 BRACKET, 4 BOLT & 4
WASHER.

processStep.description: -ALTERNATOR TO ENGINE-TITAN-

instructions.line: -ALTERNATOR TO ENGINE RM695-
ASSEMBLE 1 ALTERNATOR SUB TO ENGINE WITH 1 BRACKET AND EXISTING
4 BOLTS & 4 WASHERS.

processStep.description: ORS AR MATERIAL TO ENGINE SUB

instructions.line: ORS AR MATERIAL TO ENGINE SUB
ASSEMBLE 1 BRACKET TO ENGINE WITH 3 BOLTS & 3 WASHERS
ASSEMBLE 1 VALVE TO BRACKET WITH 2 BOLTS & 2 WASHERS. ASSEMBLE 1
ELBOW ,1 O-RING . ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE WITH 1 CLIP.
NOTE: USE THE BOLTS ON THE ENGINE. ASSEMBLE 1 PIPE CONNECTOR & 1
O-RING PER PRINT.
CONNECT HARNESSES PER PRINT
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO VALVE WITH 1 O RING. ASSEMBLE 1 O RING,1
ADAPTER,1 ELBOW WITH 1 O-RING.

processStep.description: ORS AR MATERIAL TO ENGINE SUB

instructions.line: ORS AR MATERIAL TO ENGINE SUB
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW AND 1 CONNECTOR TO VALVE ON ENGINE.
ASSEMBLE 1 PLATE TO THE SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH 1 SEAL, 2 BOLTS
AND 2 WASHERS.
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THE ELBOW ON THE TOP OF THE VALVE.

processStep.description: SECURE ORS HOSE TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: SECURE ORS HOSE TO ENGINE TITAN
SECURE THE HOSE PREVIOUSLY ASSEMBLED TO THE ORS VALVE TO THE
PLATE PREVIOUSLY ASSEMBLED TO THE ENGINE USING EXISTING
HARDWARE.
SECURE THE PLATE WITH THE ELBOW USING MOUNTING HARDWARE.
SECURE TO THE ENGINE BOSS WITH 1 CLIP, 1 BOLT AND 1 WASHER.
SECURE TO THE VALVE COVER WITH 1 CLIP, 1 BOLT AND 1 WASHER.
SECURE TO THE FLAT SPOT ON THE LH SIDE OF THE ENGINE IN THE TOP
FRON HOLE USING 1 CLIP, 1 BOLT, 1 WASHER AND 1 SPACER.
CONNECT TO THE FUEL TEE WITH 1 REDUCER AND 1 NUT.

processStep.description: -GUARD GP-BELT-TITAN-

instructions.line: -GUARD GP-BELT-TITAN-
ASSEMBLE 1 GUARD WITH 2 BOLTS, 2 WASHERS, 2 SPACERS, 2
RETAINERS, 2 BOLTS, 2 WASHERS, 2 SPACERS, & 2 RETAINERS TO
ENGINE.

processStep.description: BATTERY CABLES TO RH STARTER-TITAN

instructions.line: BATTERY CABLES TO RH STARTER-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 CABLE & 1 CABLE TO RH SIDE OF ENGINE WITH 1 BOLT & 1
WASHER.
SECURE SHORTER CABLE TO STARTER AT RH SIDE OF ENGINE ROUTE &
SECURE LONGER CABLE DOWN RH SIDE OF ENGINE AND SECURE WITH 1
CLIP & 1 GROMMET WITH EXISTING HARDWARE ON ENGINE COOLER.
ASSEMBLE 2 STRAPS TO BOOT ENDS OF CABLE AS.

processStep.description: STARTER CABLE-STARTER TO JUCTION PLATE

instructions.line: STARTER CABLE-STARTER TO JUCTION PLATE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 PLATE & 1 POWER STUD TO REAR OF ENGINE USING EXISTING
HARDWARE.
ASSEMBLE 1 CABLE AS. FROM LH STARTER AND ROUTE TO PLATE. SECURE
TO ENGINE WITH 1 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 2 CLIP, 2 BOLT, 2 WASHER, 1
SPACER & 4 GROMMET. (2 CLIPS USE EXISTING HARDWARE)
SECURE BOOT TO CABLE WITH 2 STRAPS.
SECURE 1 CABLE FROM PLATE TO LH STARTER.

processStep.description: ASSEMBLE BELT GROUP TO ENGINE PULLEYS

instructions.line: ASSEMBLE BELT GROUP TO ENGINE PULLEYS
ASSEMBLE 4 BELTS TO THE 3 MAIN PULLEYS ON THE ENGINE. USE THE
TOOL THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDED TO EXTEND THE SPRINGS. ENSURE THAT
THE TOOL IS BEING USED ON THE BRACKET IN BETWEEN THE 2 SPRINGS.
ENSURE THAT ALL BELTS ARE SEATED IN THE GROOVES AND STRAIGHT
BEFORE RELEASING TENSION ON THE SPRINGS.

processStep.description: ASSEMBLE BELT GROUP TO ENGINE PULLEYS

instructions.line: ASSEMBLE BELT GROUP TO ENGINE PULLEYS
ASSEMBLE 4 BELTS TO THE 3 MAIN PULLEYS ON THE ENGINE. USE THE
TOOL THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDED TO EXTEND THE SPRINGS. ENSURE THAT
THE TOOL IS BEING USED ON THE BRACKET IN BETWEEN THE 2 SPRINGS.
ENSURE THAT ALL BELTS ARE SEATED IN THE GROOVES AND STRAIGHT
BEFORE RELEASING TENSION ON THE SPRINGS.

processStep.description: RH DISPOSAL TUBE TO ENGINE-TITAN LRC

instructions.line: RH DISPOSAL TUBE TO ENGINE-TITAN LRC
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO CENTER VALVE COVER ON THE TOP RH SIDE OF THE
ENGINE. ASSEMBLE 1 TUBE TO HOSE AND SECURE WITH 2 CLAMPS.
ASSEMBLE 1 CLIP & 1 PLATE TO BOTTOM OF TUBE AND SECURE WITH 1
BOLT, 1 BOLT, 2 WASHER, 1 WASHER & 1 NUT.

processStep.description: LH DISPOSAL TUBE TO ENGINE-TITAN LRC

instructions.line: LH DISPOSAL TUBE TO ENGINE-TITAN LRC
CONNECT 1 HOSE TO LH CENTER VALVE COVER AND PUT 2 HOSE CLAMPS ON
HOSE. LAY 1 TUBE ON THE ENGINE SO AS THOUGH IT WILL NOT FALL
OFF. THIS TUBE WILL BE CONNECTED ATER THE ENGINE IS IN THE
UNIT.
ASSEMBLE 1 BRACKET TO THE BACK OF THE BOTTOM RH OIL COOLER WITH
1 BOLT, 1 WASHER AND 1 SPACER ENSURE THE CLIP BOLT AND WASHER IS
THERE FOR LATER ASSEMBLY.

processStep.description: BATTERY CABLES TO LH STARTER-TITAN

instructions.line: BATTERY CABLES TO LH STARTER-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 CABLE & 1 CABLE TO LH SIDE OF ENGINE WITH 1 BOLT $ 1
WASHER.
SECURE SHORTER CABLE TO LH STARTER WITH EXISTING HARDWARE.
ALLOW LONGER CABLE TO HANG DOWN LOOSELY AS IT WILL BE SECURED TO
THE ENGINE MOUNT ONE IN UNIT.
SECURE BOOTS WITH 2 STRAP.

processStep.description: HOSE TO FRONT OF OIL COOLER ELBOW TITAN

instructions.line: HOSE TO FRONT OF OIL COOLER ELBOW TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THE CONNECTOR ON THE FRONT OF THE BOTTOM REAR
OIL COOLER ELBOW GOING TOWARDS THE FRONT OF THE TRUCK.

processStep.description: HOSE TO BACK OF OIL COOLER ELBOW TITAN

instructions.line: HOSE TO BACK OF OIL COOLER ELBOW TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THE BACK OF THE BOTTOM REAR
OIL COOLER ELBOW GOING TOWARDS THE REAR OF THE TRUCK WITH
EXISTING FLANGE, BOLTS AND WASHERS.

processStep.description: TUBE TO BOTTOM OIL COOLER TITAN

instructions.line: TUBE TO BOTTOM OIL COOLER TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 TUBE ASSEMBLY TO THE FRONT PORT ON THE BOTTOM OIL
COOLER WITH 1 O-RING, 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS GOING TOWARDS THE
REAR OF THE ENGINE ON THE RH SIDE.

processStep.description: SECURE COOLER TUBE TO TC TITAN

instructions.line: SECURE COOLER TUBE TO TC TITAN
SECURE THE TUBE ASSEMBLY PREVIOUSLY ASSEMBLED TO THE OIL COOLER
TO THE TOP RH SIDE OF THE TC WITH 1 PLATE, 1 CLIP, 1 BOLT AND 1
WASHER. THE CLIP WILL BE SECURED WITH THE TC MOUNTING HARDWARE.
ASSEMBLE 2 FLANGES WITH 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS TO THE BACK SIDE
OF THE TUBE FOR LATER ASSEMBLY.

processStep.description: SECURE TUBE TO THE RH SIDE OF TC TITAN

instructions.line: SECURE TUBE TO THE RH SIDE OF TC TITAN
SECURE THE TUBE JUST BEFOR THE JOINT OF THE HOSE TUBE TO THE TOP
BOSS ON THE TOP RH SIDE OF THE CONVERTER WITH 1 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 1
BOLT, 1 WASHER AND 1 SPACER.

processStep.description: BOTTOM OIL COOLER ELBOW TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: BOTTOM OIL COOLER ELBOW TO ENGINE TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW SUB TO THE BOTTOM REAR PORT OF THE BOTTOM OIL
COOLER ON THE RH SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH 1 PLATE, 1 O-RING, 1
O-RING AND 4 BOLTS.

processStep.description: INSTALL LH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE

instructions.line: INSTALL LH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE
AFTER MOVING THE ENGINE TO THE STAND USING LIFTING DEVICE
ASSEMBLE THE LH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE WITH 1 MOUNT, 1
SUPPORT, 2 BOLTS, 4 BOLTS, 6 WASHERS, 3 BOLTS AND 3 WASHERS.
NOTE: LEAVE SHIPPING COVER ON ENGINE UNTIL ENGINE IS READY TO
HAVE TORQUE CONVERTER MOUNTED.
ASSEMBLE REAR ENGINE MOUNTS TO THE ENGINE PER PRINT
SPECIFICATIONS.

component.note: NOTE: TORQUE TO 1050 +/- 150 Nm, MATING SURFACES MUST BE FREE

processStep.description: INSTALL RH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE

instructions.line: INSTALL RH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE
AFTER MOVING THE ENGINE TO THE STAND USING LIFTING DEVICE
ASSEMBLE THE RH REAR MOTOR MOUNT TO ENGINE WITH 1 MOUNT, 1
SUPPORT, 2 BOLTS, 4 BOLTS, 6 WASHERS, 3 BOLTS AND 3 WASHERS.
NOTE: LEAVE SHIPPING COVER ON ENGINE UNTIL ENGINE IS READY TO
HAVE TORQUE CONVERTER MOUNTED.
ASSEMBLE REAR ENGINE MOUNTS TO THE ENGINE PER PRINT
SPECIFICATIONS.

component.note: NOTE: TORQUE TO 1050 +/- 150 Nm, MATING SURFACES MUST BE FREE

processStep.description: PT OIL COOLER ELBOW TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: PT OIL COOLER ELBOW TO ENGINE TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 ELBOW SUB TO THE BOTTOM FRONT PORT OF THE OIL COOLER
ON THE RH SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH 1 O-RING AND 4 BOLTS.

processStep.description: COOLER TUBE TO ELBOW TITAN

instructions.line: COOLER TUBE TO ELBOW TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 TUBE ASSEMBLE PREVIOUSLY ASSEMBLED TO THE OIL COOLER
ON THE RH SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH EXISTING 2 FLANGES, 4 BOLTS
AND 4 WASHERS AND 1 O-RING.

processStep.description: COOLER TUBE TO TC TITAN

instructions.line: COOLER TUBE TO TC TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 THE OPPOSITE END OF THE TUBE ASSEMBLED TO THE OIL
COOLER THE TC ON THE BACK LH SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH 1 O-RING
AND EXISTING FLANGES, BOLTS AND WASHERS.
ASSEMBLE 1 SENSOR TO BOTTOM OF TUBE AND CONNECT INTO ENGINE
HARNESS.

processStep.description: BLOCK AND HOSE TUBE TO TC TITAN

instructions.line: BLOCK AND HOSE TUBE TO TC TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 BLOCK TO THE TOP PORT ON THE LH SIDE OF THE TC WITH 1
O-RING, 2 FLANGES, 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS. SECURE 1 TUBE
ASSEMBLY WITH 1 O-RING ALONG WITH THE BLOCK.
ASSEMBLE 2 FLANGES WITH 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS TO THE TOP OF THE
BLOCK.

processStep.description: SHORT COOLER HOSE TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: SHORT COOLER HOSE TO ENGINE TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THE REAR PORT ON THE TOP COOLER WITH 1O-RING,
2 FLANGES, 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS.
THIS HOSE SHOULD BE ROUTED STRAIGHT TO THE BACK OF THE ENGINE
FOR LATER ASSEMBLY TO THE T/C.

processStep.description: -BRAKE PUMP TO ENGINE TITAN-

instructions.line: -BRAKE PUMP TO ENGINE TITAN-
USE NYLON STRAP TO LIFT PUMP INTO PLACE
RECORD THE SERIAL NUMBER ON THE BRAKE PUMP INTO MES TRACEABILITY
PRIOR TO ASSEMBLY.
PICK UP 1 PUMP GP-BRAKE. ASSEMBLE BRAKE PUMP TO REAR OF ENGINE
WITH SEAL, BOLTS, & WASHERS SENT WITH PUMP.
NOTE: TIGHTEN TO 1E0279B

processStep.description: -BRAKE PUMP SUB TO ENGINE TITAN-

instructions.line: -BRAKE PUMP SUB TO ENGINE TITAN-
USE NYLON STRAP TO LIFT PUMP INTO PLACE
PICK UP 1 PUMP GP-BRAKE. ASSEMBLE BRAKE PUMP TO REAR OF ENGINE
WITH SEAL, BOLTS, & WASHERS SENT WITH PUMP.
NOTE: TIGHTEN TO 1E0279B

processStep.description: -STEERING PUMP SUB TO ENGINE TITAN-

instructions.line: -STEERING PUMP SUB TO ENGINE TITAN-
USE NYLON STRAP TO LIFT PUMP INTO PLACE
RECORD THE SERIAL NUMBER ON THE STEERING PUMP IN MES
TRACEABILITY PRIOR TO ASSEMBLY.
PICK UP STEERING PUMP SUB. ASSEMBLE STEERING PUMP SUB TO REAR
OF ENGINE WITH EXISTING SEAL, BOLTS, & WASHERS SENT WITH PUMP.
NOTE: TIGHTEN TO 1E0279B

processStep.description: FLANGES TO BRAKE PUMP TITAN

instructions.line: FLANGES TO BRAKE PUMP TITAN
ASSEMBLE 2 FLANGES WITH 4 BOLTS AND 4 WASHERS TO THE BACK RH
SIDE OF THE BRAKE PUMP. LEAVE BOLTS LOOSE FOR LATER ASSEMBLY.

processStep.description: ASSEMBLE REAR TRANS OIL COOLER HOSE

instructions.line: ASSEMBLE COOLER TUBE HOSE TO OIL COOLER
ASSEMBLE 1 HOSE TO THE BACK PORT ON THE OIL COOLER LOACTED ON
THE RH SIDE OF THE ENGINE WITH 2 CLAMPS.

processStep.description: SECURE TUBES UNDER TC TITAN

instructions.line: SECURE TUBES UNDER TC TITAN
SECURE 1 STRAP TO THE BOTTOM BOLT ON THE TC. SECURE THE 2 TUBES
RUNNING IN BETWEEN THE ENGINE AND TC WITH 1 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 1
GROMMET, 1 CLIP, 1 CLIP, 1 GROMMET, 1 BOLTS 2 WAHERS AND 1 NUT.

processStep.description: ASSEMBLE CCEM MODULE TO ENGINE TITAN

instructions.line: ASSEMBLE CCEM MODULE TO ENGINE TITAN
USE LIFTING DEVICE TO PUT THE CCEM MODULE ON THE TOP OF THE
ENGINE AND SECURE WITH BOLTS TO THE TOP OF THE ENGINE.

processStep.description: LINES GP EXH FROM TURBO TO CCEM LH TITAN

instructions.line: LINES GP EXH FROM TURBO TO CCEM LH TITAN
USE THE FOLLOWING SEQUENCE FOR INSTALLING THE LINES GP.
1. INSTRUCTIONS FOR BELLOWS ALIGNMENT:
USE THE BELLOWS ALIGNMENT TOOL TO ENSURE 1 MINIMUM CONVOLUTION
TO CONVOLUTION CLEARANCE AFTER MOUNTING.
2.INSTRUCTIONS FOR TIGHTENING SEQUENCE:
ASSEMBLE LOOSLEY ALL COMPONENTS FROM ENGINE OUTLET TO
AFTERTREATMENT INLET.
TIGHTEN V-BAND CLAMP (ENGINE)
TIGHTEN NORMA SEC BALL CLAMPS (CCEM AND OPPOSITE TUBE)
TIGHTEN TORCA ACCUSEAL SLIP CLAMP (THE LAST ONE)

processStep.description: LINES GP EXH FROM TURBO TO CCEM RH TITAN

instructions.line: LINES GP EXH FROM TURBO TO CCEM RH TITAN
USE THE FOLLOWING SEQUENCE FOR INSTALLING THE LINES GP.
1. INSTRUCTIONS FOR BELLOWS ALIGNMENT:
USE THE BELLOWS ALIGNMENT TOOL TO ENSURE 1 MINIMUM CONVOLUTION
TO CONVOLUTION CLEARANCE AFTER MOUNTING.
2.INSTRUCTIONS FOR TIGHTENING SEQUENCE:
ASSEMBLE LOOSLEY ALL COMPONENTS FROM ENGINE OUTLET TO
AFTERTREATMENT INLET.
TIGHTEN V-BAND CLAMP (ENGINE)
TIGHTEN NORMA SEC BALL CLAMPS (CCEM AND OPPOSITE TUBE)
TIGHTEN TORCA ACCUSEAL SLIP CLAMP (THE LAST ONE)

processStep.description: EXHAUST TUBES TO CCEM MODULE-TITAN

instructions.line: EXHAUST TUBES TO CCEM MODULE-TITAN
ASSEMBLE 2 TUBE TO CCEM MODULE ON TOP OF ENGINE AND SECURE WITH
2 CLAMP.

processStep.description: OCV FILTER HOSE TO RH OIL PAN TITAN

instructions.line: OCV FILTER HOSE TO RH OIL PAN TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 PC OF BULK HOSE TO THE TUBE ON THE ENGINE OIL PAN
WITH 1 HOSE CLAMP.

processStep.description: OCV FILTER HOSE TO LH OIL PAN TITAN

instructions.line: OCV FILTER HOSE TO LH OIL PAN TITAN
ASSEMBLE 1 PC OF BULK HOSE TO THE TUBE ON THE ENGINE OIL PAN
WITH 1 HOSE CLAMP.

processStep.description: APPLY NORTH AMERICAN FILMS TO ENGINE-TTN

instructions.line: APPLY NORTH AMERICAN FILMS TO ENGINE-TTN
APPLY ALL NORTH AMERICAN FILMS TO THE ENGINE ACCORDING TO THE
VISUAL AIDS.
